The ſhepin brenning with the blakè ſmoke Perhaps, for ſhepyn we ſhould read chepyn, or cheping, i. e. a town, a place of trade. This line is therefore to repreſent, A City on fire. In Wickliffe's bible we have, "It is lyk to children ſittynge in CHEPYNGE." 
